      "role": "user",
      "content": "that makes sense. i'm a bit nervous about opening it up because i've heard people call these weird electrical glitches \"gremlins\" or something like that. is there anything else besides a capacitor that would cause that clicking and humming, or is it usually just a simple part failing?",
      "source": "evaluator"
